[Spain has been having ongoing West Nile virus (WNV) transmission over the course of this summer (2020). WNV has been endemic in this region of Spain for at least 2 decades. It is usually transmitted in this locality by _Culex pipiens_ and _Culex [perexiquus]_ mosquitoes.

Interestingly, no mention is made of WNV infection in horses in the above report or in previous ones this year (2020). Equine cases usually occur before human ones do. There is a vaccine available for equine animals, but not for humans, so vector mosquito control and avoidance of mosquito bites are the only measures available to prevent infection in people. - Mod.TY

